01/06/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Two soldiers and three village guards were killed in a clash with Kurdish rebels in eastern Turkey, authorities in Ankara reported on Wednesday (31 May). Five other village guards were injured in the incident, which occurred during a military operation in a mountainous area of Sirnak province near the Iraqi border.
In other news, local media reports Thursday suggest police uncovered an assassination plot against Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan. A total of 11 people reportedly were arrested, including several active members of the army or reserves. (Sabah, Milliyet, Aksan - 01/06/06; Reuters - 31/05/06)
